	Kroket release 0.8.1

These are the release notes for Kroket version 0.8.1
Read them carefully, as they tell you what this is all about.


WHAT IS KROKET ?

 Kroket is an interactive directed graph visualization tool.
 It allows you to progressively unfold the graph and to expand/collapse
 groups of nodes.

 Kroket is a free software, it is licensed under the GNU GPL.
 Have a look at the `COPYING' file for details.

 In order to run Kroket, you need the Qt library, as well as its development
 packages if you compile it by yourself.


HOW TO INSTALL ?

 Instructions to install kroket are details in the `INSTALL' file.


HOW TO RUN ?

 Once you have compiled the program, you should be able to run it by
 invoking `kroket'. Don't hesitate to try one of the files contained in
 the `tests' subdirectory to view what Kroket's capable of.
